snippet.textDisplay: How about a titanium bat?  It is supposed to have a molecular memory and resistant to denting or being crushed.  My father worked with it on aircraft in the Navy, and in the early years, it was used to put on the leading edge of the wing.  What they found was that bending titanium sheet over the wing and riveting it into place, it would pull the rivets out.  Also we were told that the Soviets were able to accomplish multi pass titanium welding to build the Alpha Class subs by welding in an inert room.  Oooo a show on the metallurgy of titanium would be cool.
